<paragraph id="IFRS17_74" base="F55666506" principles="yes"><paranum>74</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 17"/><data name="paranum" value="74"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS17_P0287">An entity shall derecognise an <xref base="F55666957" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0532">insurance contract<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0186"/></ph></xref> when, and only when: </p><ol id="IFRS17_L0054" base="F55666508" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="IFRS17_P0288" base="F55666509">it is extinguished, ie when the obligation specified in the insurance contract expires or is discharged or cancelled;  or</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="IFRS17_P0289" base="F55666511">any of the conditions in <xref id="IFRS17_X0342" base="F59233736" href="IFRS17_g72-73.dita#IFRS17_g72-73/IFRS17_g72-73_TI">paragraph 72</xref> are met.</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>